OL,3,C50 Years On: The Death Sentence, the
OL,4,CDictator, and the Cardiff Pool
OL,6,FLiving in Uganda at the time was Denis
OL,7,FHills, a British academic and writer.
OL,8,FHills had written a book in which he
OL,9,Fcriticised Amin. Furious, the dictator
OL,10,Fhad Hills arrested and charged with
OL,11,Fespionage. He was sentenced to death
OL,12,Fby firing squad, and suddenly found
OL,13,Fhimself the centre of an international
OL,14,Fdiplomatic crisis.
OL,16,FEnter the third figure in this
OL,17,Fextraordinary story: Jim Callaghan,
OL,18,Fthen Foreign Secretary and Cardiff MP.
