OL,3,C50 Years On: The Death Sentence, the
OL,4,CDictator, and the Cardiff Pool
OL,6,FInitial diplomatic approaches had
OL,7,Ffailed. Amin, ever theatrical, issued
OL,8,Fa chilling ultimatum at a press
OL,9,Fconference:
OL,11,F"If the Foreign Secretary is not here
OL,12,Ften days from tomorrow, we will then
OL,13,Fconsider when to execute Hills by the
OL,14,Ffiring squad."
OL,16,FCallaghan later said he "risked his
OL,17,Freputation" by agreeing to go. Prime
OL,18,FMinister Harold Wilson warned him that
OL,19,Fhe was moving too fast, acting without
OL,20,Fenough caution. But Callaghan went.
