OL,3,C50 Years On: The Death Sentence, the
OL,4,CDictator, and the Cardiff Pool
OL,6,FThe conversation, surreal in tone
OL,7,Fgiven the life or death stakes, drifts
OL,8,Finto talk of Wales. Amin affirms his
OL,9,Flove of Wales, saying he would spend
OL,10,Fhis weekends in the country, admiring
OL,11,Fhow green it is and the friendliness
OL,12,Fof the people. Asked by Callaghan if
OL,13,Fit reminds him of Uganda, Amin says it
OL,14,Fdoes.
OL,16,FLater, posing for photographers with
OL,17,Fhis son, Amin points at him saying to
OL,18,FCallaghan:J"He will come to Wales."
OL,19,FCallaghan smiles: "I will teach him
OL,20,FWelsh."
